The paper applies deep learning to the task of automated cardiac auscultation, which involves recognizing abnormalities in heart sounds. This task involves signal processing and classification, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.SD (Signal Processing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are known for their use of deep learning techniques for image and signal processing tasks.
